The paper deals with the problem of active machine learning, specifically in the context of target localization. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of sequential and joint policies for constructing questions suggests that the paper may also belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the application of the framework to robotics suggests that the paper may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
